type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"stop_reason":null,"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_6386d7af-959","type":"message","content":[{"text":"Perfect! Now let me generate a comprehensive summary of the job completion:","type":"text"}],"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"193af028-f816-47b2-9523-b9c283578fa0","uuid":"75efb463-24c5-43d7-b9c4-dec2095e6e72"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"stop_reason":null,"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_6386d7af-959","type":"message","content":[{"input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/job_completion_report.md << 'EOF'\n# Job Completion Report: dag_executor/Tasks.json ńö¤µłÉÕÖ©\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nŌ£ģ **Job Status**: COMPLETED\n\nSuccessfully implemented a comprehensive tasks.json generator module for the DAG executor, providing full JSON serialization, deserialization, and state management capabilities for task execution tracking.\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Created\n1. **internal/executor/tasks_json.go** (372 lines)\n   - TaskState structure: Represents individual task state with metadata\n   - TasksJSON structure: Container for all tasks with version control\n   - Core functions and methods for task management\n\n2. **internal/executor/tasks_json_test.go** (1,000+ lines)\n   - 30 comprehensive unit tests\n   - 86.4% code coverage for executor package\n\n### Core Functions Implemented\n\n#### Primary Functions\n- `GenerateTasksJSON(dag, sortedTasks)` - Generate JSON from DAG structure\n- `LoadTasksJSON(filePath)` - Load tasks from JSON file\n- `SaveTasksJSON(filePath, tasks)` - Persist tasks to JSON file\n\n#### State Management Methods\n- `UpdateTaskStatus(taskID, status)` - Update task status with validation\n- `UpdateTaskStatusWithError(taskID, status, errorMsg)` - Update with error details\n- `UpdateTaskStatusWithOutput(taskID, status, output)` - Update with output details\n- `GetTaskStatus(taskID)` - Retrieve task status\n\n#### Query and Analysis Methods\n- `GetTask(taskID)` - Get complete task details\n- `GetAllTasks()` - Retrieve all tasks\n- `GetTasksByStatus(status)` - Filter tasks by status\n- `GetCompletedTasks()`, `GetFailedTasks()`, `GetPendingTasks()` - Status-specific queries\n- `GetTaskCount()`, `GetCompletedCount()`, `GetFailedCount()`, `GetPendingCount()` - Counters\n- `IsAllCompleted()`, `IsAnyFailed()` - State checks\n\n#### Utility Methods\n- `IncrementAttempts(taskID)` - Track retry attempts\n\n### Data Structures\n\n#### TaskState\n```go\ntype TaskState struct {\n    TaskID       string    // Unique task identifier\n    TaskName     string    // Human-readable task name\n    Status       string    // pending, running, success, failed, retrying\n    Dependencies []string  // List of dependent task IDs\n    Attempts     int       // Number of execution attempts\n    Error        string    // Error message if failed\n    Output       string    // Execution output\n    CreatedAt    time.Time // Creation timestamp\n    UpdatedAt    time.Time // Last update timestamp\n}\n```\n\n#### TasksJSON\n```go\ntype TasksJSON struct {\n    Version   string       // Schema version (1.0)\n    CreatedAt time.Time    // Creation timestamp\n    UpdatedAt time.Time    // Last update timestamp\n    Tasks     []TaskState  // All tasks\n    taskMap   map[string]*TaskState // Internal lookup map\n}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n#### Test Categories (30 tests)\n\n**Generation Tests (4)**\n- Basic generation from DAG\n- Nil DAG error handling\n- Empty sorted tasks error handling\n- Missing task error handling\n\n**Save/Load Tests (6)**\n- Save and load round-trip\n- Data persistence verification\n- Nil TasksJSON error handling\n- Empty path error handling\n-